cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.IR 

The paper focuses on organizing multimedia data in video surveillance systems using face verification algorithms and deep convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper deals with machine learning techniques for face recognition, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also discusses the use of hierarchical agglomerative clustering, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the accuracy and security of the proposed approach, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper deals with the estimation of gender and age, which falls under the category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
